  "metadata": {
    "title": "CVE-2022-0516 kernel: missing check in ioctl allows kernel memory read/write (important)",
    "reference": [
      {
        "ref_id": "CVE-2022-0516",
        "ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2022-0516",
        "source": "CVE"
      }
    ],
    "description": "DOCUMENTATION: A vulnerability was found in kvm_s390_guest_sida_op in the arch/s390/kvm/kvm-s390.c function in KVM for s390 in the Linux kernel. This flaw allows a local attacker with a normal user privilege to obtain unauthorized memory write access. \n            \n            MITIGATION: As the kvm.ko kernel module will be auto-loaded when required, its use can be disabled  by preventing the module from loading with the following instructions:\n\n# echo \"install kvm /bin/true\" >> /etc/modprobe.d/disable-kvm.conf\n\nIf the system requires this module to work correctly, this mitigation may not be suitable.\n\nIf you need further assistance, see the KCS article https://access.redhat.com/solutions/41278 or contact Red Hat Global Support Services.",
